ABUJA (SundiataPost) – A total of 407 Nigerians have died from COVID-19 infections since since the index case in Nigeria was confirmed in Lagos on 27 February 2020. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) made this known late on Saturday night on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov.The agency also reported 501 new cases, even as it informed that 5,101 infected persons have been treated and discharged.The total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria, according to the report, is 15,682. The full report reads: 501 new cases of #COVID19 Lagos-195FCT-50Kano-42Kaduna-27Edo-26Oyo-22Imo-21Gombe-17Benue-12Enugu-12Delta-11Anambra-11Ebonyi-10Nasarawa-9Ogun-9Bauchi-8Kebbi-4Akwa Ibom-3Jigawa-3Katsina-3Yobe-2Borno-2Kwara-1Ondo-1 15682 confirmed5101 discharged407 deaths See state by state breakdown below: ABUJA - In what is gradually creating panic in Nigeria the Coronavirus pandemic has increased alarmingly to 407 confirmed cases, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported late on Wednesday. The NCDC reported 34 new cases, the highest in a single day since Nigeria's index case in February.Lagos remains… April 15, 2020 In "News" The Lagos State Government on Wednesday announced the death of another COVID-19 related patient, barely 24 hours after the sixth death was recorded. It also announced that 25 new cases were recorded, bringing the total confirmed cases in the state to 217. The State Ministry of Health made this known… April 15, 2020 In "News" The Federal Government says there is no new case from 61 contacts of the index case of Coronavirus (COVID-19) in the country, NAN reports. The Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire, at a media update on COVID-19 in Abuja on Friday, said the contacts had been monitored since the announcement of… March 6, 2020 In "Health"